The problem here is that we're comparing a boolean value with a string, whi
which will always result in `false`. Here is the corrected program:

```tundra
val cached = { active: false };
var current = { active: true };

if (cached.active) {
  print("send");
} else {
  print("skip");
}
```
This code should now correctly output "send" because `cached.active` is a b
boolean and in this case it's `false`, so the program executes the 'else' b
branch and prints "skip".
